-- Putin May Visit Poland Today Before Signing of Gas Deal, Polsat Reports
-- B y   M a c i e j   M a r t e w i c z
-- 2010-10-28T06:04:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/putin-may-visit-poland-today-before-signing-of-gas-deal-polsat-reports.html
Russian Prime Minister Vladimir
Putin may fly to Poland today in a visit linked to tomorrow’s
signing of a new long-term deal on delivery of Russian natural
gas, Warsaw-based Polsat News reported today.  Putin’s trip, which wasn’t previously announced, coincides
with the presence in Warsaw of Russian Foreign Minister Sergei
Lavrov, who arrived to help prepare for Russian President Dmitry
Medvedev’s planned state visit on Dec. 6.  The Foreign Ministry couldn’t be reached for comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maciej Martewicz in Warsaw at 
 mmartewicz@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David McQuaid at 
 dmcquaid1@bloomberg.net  